write a JavaScript program to generate and print out the ascii character and hexadecimal codes for 0 to 7f
Here's an example of how you can write a JavaScript program that generates and prints out the ASCII characters and their corresponding hexadecimal codes from 0 to 7F (inclusive):
```javascript
for(let i = 0; i <= 127; i++) { // loop through all ASCII characters up to 7F
    let asciiCode = String.fromCharCode(i); // convert the character code to a string
    console.log(`ASCII Code: ${asciiCode}`);
}
```This program will output something like this in your console:
```
ASCII Code: \u0001
ASCII Code: \u0002
ASCII Code: \u0003
... and so on, up to ASCII code 7F.
